The Wajir county assembly has impeached Wajir governor Mahamud Abdi Mohamed.37 MCAs voted in favour of the motion to impeach the governor while 10 of them opposed. two mca's were absent during the vote. governor Abdi is accused of abuse of office among other allegations. the first-term governor is also facing allegations of financial impropriety, gross misconduct and violation of the constitution. governor Abdi's fate now lies with the senate, which will either convict or acquit him over the impeachment motion. earlier in the day, there was tension in the streets of Wajir town as residents awaited the decision of the county assembly, with heavy security deployed around the county assembly as well as the governor's office.